President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to announce changes to the National Executive at the Union Buildings, Pretoria, at three o’clock on Thursday afternoon. In a statement issued on Thursday morning, the presidency said “these changes have been occasioned by the passing away in September 2018 of the Minister of Environmental Affairs, Ms Edna Molewa, and the more recent resignation of the Minister of Home Affairs, Mr Malusi Gigaba.” — News 24 Watch the announcement live: 